{# templates/roadmaps/real-state/analyze-rental-property.html.twig #}
{% extends 'base-roadmaps.html.twig' %}

{% block stylesheets %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_link_tags('real_state_css') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block javascripts %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_script_tags('real_state_js') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="container">
        <!-- Article Hero -->
        <div class="article-hero animate" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2f2a24 0%, #5e4b3f 100%);">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <div class="hero-icon" style="background-color: var(--real-estate-color);">
                    <i class="fas fa-chart-simple"></i>
                </div>
                <h1>How to Analyze a Rental Property <span>A Practical Template</span></h1>
                <p class="hero-description">
                    Use our simple template to run the numbers on any rental property. We'll show you what to look for and what numbers really matter.
                </p>
                <div class="phase-tag" style="background-color: rgba(225,112,85,0.2); color: #f7b9a9;">
                    <i class="fas fa-layer-group"></i> Phase 3: Practical Execution · 10 min read
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <section class="animate">
            <h2 class="section-title">📋 The One‑Page Rental Analysis</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                Every great real estate investor uses a consistent method to evaluate deals. This template walks you through the key numbers:
                <strong>income, expenses, cash flow, and returns.</strong> Once you master it, you can analyze any property in 15 minutes.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Template Steps Grid -->
        <div class="rule-grid animate">
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-dollar-sign"></i> 1. Income</h4>
                <p>Gross rental income – include rent, laundry, storage, parking. Use market rents, not seller's claims.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-minus-circle"></i> 2. Vacancy</h4>
                <p>Subtract a vacancy allowance (5–10% of gross income). This cushions against lost rent.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-tools"></i> 3. Operating Expenses</h4>
                <p>Property taxes, insurance, maintenance (1% of value/year), property management (8–10%), utilities, HOA, reserves.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-hand-holding-usd"></i> 4. Net Operating Income (NOI)</h4>
                <p>Gross income – vacancy – operating expenses. This is the property's profit before debt service.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> 5. Cash Flow & Returns</h4>
                <p>Subtract mortgage payment from NOI to get monthly cash flow. Then calculate cap rate (NOI/price) and cash‑on‑cash ROI (annual cash flow / down payment).</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Deeper Dive Card -->
        <div class="card animate">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-calculator"></i> The 1% Rule and 50% Rule</h3>
            <p><strong>1% Rule:</strong> Monthly rent should be at least 1% of purchase price. Quick screen, not a guarantee.</p>
            <p><strong>50% Rule:</strong> Operating expenses (excluding mortgage) will be about 50% of gross income. Helps estimate cash flow quickly.</p>
            <p style="background: var(--light-gray); padding: 15px; border-radius: 12px;">
                <strong>Example:</strong> $200,000 property, $2,000/month rent → passes 1% rule. Expenses ~$1,000/month (50% rule), mortgage ~$900 → cash flow $100/month. Use the template below for precise numbers.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Interactive Tool: Rental Analysis Template (disabled for non-logged-in) -->
        <div class="card animate" id="rental-analysis-tool">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-table"></i> Interactive: Rental Property Analysis Template</h3>
            <p>Fill in the numbers below to calculate NOI, cap rate, cash flow, and ROI.</p>

            <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Purchase Price ($) <span id="priceValAnalysis">200000</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="priceAnalysis" min="50000" max="1000000" value="200000" step="5000" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Down Payment (%) <span id="downPercentValAnalysis">20</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="downPercentAnalysis" min="3" max="50" value="20" step="1" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Interest Rate (%) <span id="rateValAnalysis">6.5</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="rateAnalysis" min="2" max="10" value="6.5" step="0.125" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Loan Term (years) </label>
                    <select id="termAnalysis" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                        <option value="15">15 years</option>
                        <option value="30" selected>30 years</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Monthly Rent ($) <span id="rentValAnalysis">1800</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="rentAnalysis" min="500" max="5000" value="1800" step="50" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Vacancy Rate (%) <span id="vacancyValAnalysis">5</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="vacancyAnalysis" min="0" max="20" value="5" step="1" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Property Tax (%/year) <span id="taxValAnalysis">1.0</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="taxAnalysis" min="0.5" max="3" value="1.0" step="0.1" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Insurance ($/year) <span id="insValAnalysis">1200</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="insuranceAnalysis" min="300" max="5000" value="1200" step="100" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Maintenance (%/year) <span id="maintValAnalysis">1.0</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="maintAnalysis" min="0.5" max="3" value="1.0" step="0.1" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Property Management (%) <span id="pmValAnalysis">8</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="pmAnalysis" min="0" max="15" value="8" step="1" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Other Monthly Expenses ($) <span id="otherValAnalysis">50</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="otherAnalysis" min="0" max="500" value="50" step="10" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
                <button id="analyzeRental" class="btn-outline">Analyze Property</button>
            </div>

            <div id="analysisResult" style="margin-top: 25px; padding: 20px; background: var(--light-color); border-radius: 12px;">
                <p>Adjust the values and click the button.</p>
            </div>

            <p class="pro-tip" style="margin-top: 15px;">
                <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> This template uses standard formulas. Adjust percentages to match your market. Always verify numbers with actual data and consult a professional.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Quiz Section -->
        {% if app.user and quiz is defined and quiz %}
            {# Logged in user – quiz already taken #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" style="background: #2f2a24;">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">🧠 You've already taken this quiz</h3>
                <p style="color: #e2e8f0; font-size: 1.2rem;">
                    Your score: <strong>{{ quiz.quizzScore }}%</strong>
                </p>
                <p style="color: #cbd5e0;">
                    You can retake the quiz to improve your score. Click the button below to reset it.
                </p>
                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'analyze-rental-property', retake: 1 }) }}"
                       class="btn"
                       style="background-color: #e17055; color: white; text-decoration: none;">
                        Retake Quiz
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        {% else %}
            {# Show quiz (interactivity blocked by JS if not logged in) #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" data-page-id="{{ page.id }}" style="background: #2f2a24;">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">📝 Test Your Knowledge: Rental Property Analysis</h3>

                <div class="quiz-question">1. What does NOI stand for?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="1">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Net Operating Interest</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Net Operating Income</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">New Owner Investment</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">National Occupancy Index</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">2. The 1% rule states that monthly rent should be at least what percentage of the purchase price?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="2">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">0.5%</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">1%</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">2%</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">5%</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">3. Which of the following is NOT typically subtracted before calculating NOI?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="3">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Property taxes</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Insurance</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Mortgage payments</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Maintenance</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">4. If a property costs $250,000 and generates $2,000/month rent, what is its gross rent multiplier (GRM)?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="4">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">125</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">10.4</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">8.3</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">0.008</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">5. Cash‑on‑cash return measures:</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="5">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Return on total property value</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Return on the actual cash invested (down payment)</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Return after selling</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Annual appreciation</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <button id="quiz-submit" class="btn" style="background-color: var(--real-estate-color);">Get score & submit</button>
                </div>
                <div class="quiz-result"></div>
            </div>
        {% endif %}

        <!-- Next Steps in Phase 3 -->
        <section style="margin: 60px 0;">
            <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: center;">📘 Complete Phase 3: Practical Execution</h2>
            <div class="next-steps">
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'saving-for-down-payment' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-piggy-bank"></i>
                    <h3>Saving for Your Down Payment</h3>
                    <p>A step‑by‑step plan to build your fund.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'mortgage-guide' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i>
                    <h3>How to Get a Mortgage</h3>
                    <p>Credit, pre‑approval, and loan types.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'first-time-buyer-programs' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-hand-holding-heart"></i>
                    <h3>First‑Time Buyer Programs</h3>
                    <p>Grants and assistance you may qualify for.</p>
                </a>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
